Kia ora Grant,

As discussed on Monday, could you please provide, as soon as possible, the =
full list of tests performed during the 17 October site visit, together wit=
h the raw data as it becomes available, and then the formal reports when is=
sued. This is to accelerate the identification and sourcing of any missing =
tests or gaps.

Please include for the list of tests performed:


  *   Test name and brief description
  *   Sampling scope and exact locations (room/area, height, within-cavity =
vs surface)
  *   Field notes for each sample (date/time, sampler, method, pre/post-cle=
an trial where applicable)
  *   Photographs tying samples to locations and any before/after decontami=
nation trial images
  *   Any areas not tested and the rationale

Please include for the test results / raw data:


  *   As above plus
  *   Laboratory details for each sample (lab name, job ID/COC, method code=
s, analytes, units, detection limits/LOQs, QA/QC including blanks/duplicate=
s)
  *   Raw data and Numerical results of each test
  *   Results of any on-site decontamination efficacy trials (pre/post meas=
urements and method used)

Ng=C4=81 mihi,
Raffaella del Prete


