The intention is to test for smoke and chemical contamination within the wa=
ll cavities, and on the exposed surfaces downstairs. There will be a signif=
icant number of sample sites [tests] to be completed to be able to author a=
 reliable report. After initial testing is completed, our intention is to a=
pply restorative cleaning methods to targeted individual sample sites, foll=
owed by subsequent testing, post-cleaning, to provide data to measure the e=
ffectiveness of cleaning/decontamination.
All samples taken from site will require laboratory analysis before being i=
ncorporated into a report. This process may take up to 10 working days =E2=
=80=93 so we want to capture swab samples from surfaces before and after th=
e decontamination process is undertaken.

At this stage we are looking like being able to conduct this testing onsite=
, as well as CPEng site visit for assessment, on Friday October 17. Time to=
 yet be confirmed.

I am unsure from your letter attached whether Raffaella and/or other nomina=
ted parties wish to be present while this testing and assessment is being c=
onducted. Can you please confirm for me so that I can complete arrangements=
 that will suit all parties who need to be present.

Many Thanks,
Grant.

<image005.png>
Grant Metson
Regional Manager - House Assessing
